{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_2TPQpeMB4LJtm5kZfzuNNyOC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  query: string\n4\t  attachmentIds: array\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\tBuild a complete, openable live-project app from supplied material — as a PLAN → per-item BUILD\n8\tpipeline, so no single model turn has to author a whole app at once. First read the attachments, then\n9\tmake a holistic plan of the app (its tables, endpoints, reusable components, and MULTIPLE pages). From\n10\tthere each category is a `plan → implement` pair that the host fans out one file at a time: plan the\n11\ttables → write each table (with its source-derived rows), plan the endpoints → write each typed API,\n12\tplan the components → write each reusable component, plan the pages → write each page (which imports\n13\tthe components and reads the endpoints). A final node writes the persistent chat layout and reports\n14\twhat was built. Every write is its own bounded node, so a slip on one file no longer loses the build;\n15\teach writer returns `{ ok, error? }` and validates at write time. Pages use `@app/runtime` data hooks\n16\tand `@lmthing/css` design tokens only.\n17\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_xceELgSEMbLiZDXxIvlOMHdS","session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"60b632b3-2179-4106-987d-401b0e72a34b","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:22:02.194Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder structural failure"}
