 Emmanuel, really knew his stuff, kept pointing things out before we even saw them. Anyway, at the rim, on the way out, there was a Maasai lady selling beaded bracelets, and I bought two for Athena Mari. And she wanted, I think it was $25 for both, or maybe it was $20, I honestly can't remember exactly. I paid in shillings, roughly $35,000 or so. Should have written it down right there. Also, Emmanuel mentioned there's sometimes an extra ranger ti\n...\n</persisted-output>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_xceELgSEMbLiZDXxIvlOMHdS","session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"f1080180-9332-4d05-beb0-3b67b15af547","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:22:19.157Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder structural failure"}
