{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_RMfzVmvdZCMjDmzh1ShqeWiC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_endpoints\n3\toutput:\n4\t  endpoints: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, plan_tables]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tRefine the endpoint list GROUNDED in the real tables, and ASSIGN each endpoint its stable `name` — the\n11\tsingle source of truth the whole app wires through. `query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.endpoints`), and\n12\t`plan_tables` (`plan_tables.tables` — the actual tables + columns being written) are in scope. This is\n13\ta THINKING step — no writers. Plan the endpoints the pages need to read/write the real rows: at least\n14\tone read endpoint per view the app shows.\n15\t\n16\tEach endpoint is `{ name, route, purpose, tables }`:\n17\t- `name` — a UNIQUE lowercase-hyphen id (e.g. `cost-lines`, `contacts-list`, `itinerary-legs`). This\n18\t  EXACT string is BOTH the endpoint module's `export const name` AND what pages pass to `useApi(...)`.\n19\t  **This is the ONLY node that assigns names; every downstream node uses them verbatim and never\n20\t  re-derives one.** No two endpoints may share a `name`, and no two may share a `route` — scan your own\n21\t  list before resolving and rename any collision.\n22\t- `route` — the file route with its HTTP method LAST (`cost-lines/GET`, `bookings/[id]/PATCH`); methods\n23\t  GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\n24\t- `tables` — the table name(s) from `plan_tables.tables` it reads/writes.\n25\t\n26\tRead endpoints return `{ items: [...] }`, so plan read endpoints the pages consume as `data.items`.\n27\tEmit one statement:\n28\t\n29\t```typescript\n30\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n31\t  endpoints: [\n32\t    { name: '<unique-hyphen-id>', route: '<path>/GET', purpose: '<what it returns or does>', tables: [ '<table from plan_tables.tables>' ] },\n33\t  ],\n34\t});\n35\t```\n36\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_xceELgSEMbLiZDXxIvlOMHdS","session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b