{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_1np6RNL99ZQPgNSkVeqLnBPD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_components\n3\toutput:\n4\t  name: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [plan_components]\n7\tforEach: plan_components.components\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE reusable component into the LIVE project's `components/`. Your component is in `item` =\n13\t{ name, purpose, props }. Call `writeProjectComponent(item.name, src)` — the name MUST be PascalCase\n14\tand the source MUST have a DEFAULT export (the component a page renders); the writer validates both and\n15\tthat it parses as TSX, returning `{ ok, error? }`. Write the FULL `.tsx` source inline with the\n16\tarray-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern. This is presentational UI: take the record/value via props and render it —\n17\tdo NOT fetch data here (pages pass data in). STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-card`,\n18\t`text-foreground`, `text-muted`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a\n19\tstock Tailwind color (`gray-500`, `blue-600`). Import only from `react`/`@app/runtime` if needed.\n20\t`@app/runtime` exports ONLY `apiCall`, `HttpError`, `useApi`, `useApiMutation`, `useParams`, `Link`,\n21\t`navigate`, and `Chat`; do not import utility helpers such as `cn`, `clsx`, or `classNames`. Emit\n22\tone statement:\n23\t\n24\t```typescript\n25\tconst c = item;\n26\tconst src = [\n27\t  \"export default function \" + c.name + \"({ title, subtitle }: { title: string; subtitle?: string }) {\",\n28\t  \"  return (\",\n29\t  \"    <div className=\\\"rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-3\\\">\",\n30\t  \"      <p className=\\\"font-medium text-foreground\\\">{title}</p>\",\n31\t  \"      {subtitle ? <p className=\\\"text-sm text-muted\\\">{subtitle}</p> : null}\",\n32\t  \"    </div>\",\n33\t  \"  );\",\n34\t  \"}\",\n35\t].join(\"\\n\");\n36\tconst w = writeProjectComponent(c.name, src);