{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_8w1IKDu0kMkCV2dHbz4Be6b0","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_components\n3\toutput:\n4\t  components: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tPlan the REUSABLE components the pages will share — the point is UI written ONCE and imported by\n11\tseveral pages, not per-page markup. `query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.components`), and `plan_endpoints`\n12\t(`plan_endpoints.endpoints`) are in scope. This is a THINKING step — no writers. Plan a small set of\n13\tpresentational components (a `Card`, a `Row`, a `Badge`, a `StatTile`, an `EmptyState`) that render one\n14\trecord or one value and will appear on more than one page. Each `name` is PascalCase; state the `props`\n15\tit takes so the implement step and the pages agree on the shape. Emit one statement:\n16\t\n17\t```typescript\n18\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n19\t  components: [\n20\t    {\n21\t      name: '<ComponentName>',\n22\t      purpose: '<the repeated UI it renders, and which pages use it>',\n23\t      props: [ '<propName: type>' ],\n24\t    },\n25\t  ],\n26\t});\n27\t```\n28\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_xceELgSEMbLiZDXxIvlOMHdS","session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"da6e4857-6e8f-4666-b144-81715801d833","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:23:24.559Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder structural failure"}
