{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_qdzrVYXGjEKHZVYi5UcCOAgG","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_pages\n3\toutput:\n4\t  pages: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints, plan_components]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tPlan the MULTIPLE pages of the app, each wired to the real endpoints and the reusable components.\n11\t`query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.pages`), `plan_endpoints` (`plan_endpoints.endpoints` — each is\n12\t`{ name, route, purpose, tables }`), and `plan_components` (`plan_components.components`) are in scope.\n13\tThis is a THINKING step — no writers. **Every endpoint a page lists must be an existing\n14\t`plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`, copied VERBATIM — never invent a name or transform one.** Plan an\n15\t`index` home PLUS the additional views the material calls for (a list, a detail `items/[id]`, a\n16\tdashboard) — a single page is not enough. For each page, list the endpoint `name`s it reads and the\n17\tcomponents it renders, so the implement step wires real data through shared UI. Emit one statement:\n18\t\n19\t```typescript\n20\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n21\t  pages: [\n22\t    {\n23\t      route: 'index',\n24\t      purpose: '<what this page shows>',\n25\t      // endpoint NAMES, each copied verbatim from plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name:\n26\t      endpoints: [ '<endpoint name>' ],\n27\t      // component names (from plan_components) this page renders:\n28\t      components: [ '<ComponentName>' ],\n29\t    },\n30\t  ],\n31\t});\n32\t```\n33\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_xceELgSEMbLiZDXxIvlOMHdS","session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"370b68e7-f368-416e-9746-18cdd64eed79","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:23:26.300Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder structural failure"}
