{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_6HrLZlZISMC3rfIYqXMfVCQt","type":"tool_result","content":"901 statement // The build_live_project tasklist orchestrates the entire first-app build — tables, APIs, pages, and all.\n// Pass the query and attachmentIds from context so the pipeline reads the source files itself.\nconst result = await tasklist(\"build_live_project\", { query, ...context });\n904 yield {\"ts\":1784229267627,\"type\":\"yield\",\"context\":\"delegate:system-appbuilder/automator/build_live_project\",\"nodeId\":\"delegate_85_d9d08a7e\",\"kind\":\"tasklist\",\"args\":[\"build_live_project\",{\"query\":\"Organize all of Vasilis's Tanzania trip material into a cohesive project with specialist spaces and a live app. The material spans: (1) a personal notes file (tanzaniamemories.md) with trip planning details — flights, safari dates, Zanzibar stay, contacts (Richard at the office, Emmanuel the crater driver, a Maasai guide), activities, and worries; (2) a trip-costs spreadsheet with costs broken down across sheets — flights, accommodation, park fees, safari balance, tips; (3) a Ngorongoro Conservation Area official tariffs PDF with every park fee by category (entry, vehicle, camping, ranger fees); (4) a voice memo transcript from the Ngorongoro crater rim — driver Emmanuel mentioned a separate ranger tip of ~TZS 5,000 nobody told them about, and Vasilis bought two beaded bracelets for Athena Mari from a Maasai lady for ~TZS 35,000 (paid in shillings, ~$20-25), and noted to ask Richard about the ranger tip before the safari balance payment; (5) a Stone Town Zanzibar photo — an upward view through a whitewashed courtyard, a memory to keep with the trip. Build specialist spaces for each distinct topic domain (Tanzania safari logistics, Zanzibar/Stone Town, Ngorongoro park rules & fees) grounded in the provided material, and build a live app with tables for costs, contacts, trip itinerary/memories, and park fee reference, seeded from all the extracted data. The voice-memo facts (bracelets purchase, ranger tip, the \\\"ask Richard\\\" reminder) must be captured — they are not in any written file.\\n\\nBuild the complete live-project app now: write source-derived tables and rows, then write the project API and openable pages that show those rows.\\n\\nSource summary:\\nFive pieces of Tanzania trip material: a Markdown notes file covering full trip logistics (flights, safari, Zanzibar, contacts Richard & Emmanuel), a multi-sheet cost spreadsheet, the official Ngorongoro park tariff PDF, a voice memo from the crater rim (bracelet purchase ~TZS 35,000, undisclosed ranger tip ~TZS 5,000, ask-Richard reminder), and a Stone Town courtyard photo.\\n\\nFacts available only from image/audio analysis:\\nVoice-memo facts (not in any written file): (1) At Ngorongoro crater rim, a Maasai lady sold Vasilis two beaded bracelets for Athena Mari — paid in Tanzanian shillings, roughly TZS 35,000 (~$20-25). (2) Driver Emmanuel mentioned there is sometimes an extra ranger tip expected at the gate, about TZS 5,000 cash, separate from park fees — nobody told them about this before. (3) Vasilis needs to remember to ask Richard about the ranger tip before the safari balance payment. (4) Stone Town photo: an upward view through a whitewashed courtyard/light well, arched windows, classic Zanzibari architecture — a personal travel memory to keep.\\n\\nSpecialist build results:\\n[{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Tanzania Safari Logistics\\\",\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Zanzibar / Stone Town\\\",\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro Conservation Area Rules & Fees\\\",\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"\\\"}]\",\"attachmentIds\":[\"4e2420bd-e407-4e5d-87f7-da445f652f87\",\"0375c185-42d1-47a8-b669-ab31e6638150\",\"0976d8e0-1acf-4d1e-a12a-fe22ab1e6965\"]}],\"yieldId\":\"delegate_85_d9d08a7e_y1\"}\n1537 yield_resolved {\"ts\":1784229617187,\"type\":\"yield_resolved\",\"conte