{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_Z9qtoeVSBWDuwff4WsS5qyPl","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: inventory\n3\toutput:\n4\t  scopes: array\n5\trole: explore\n6\tfunctions: []\n7\tprelude: |\n8\t  const documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\tSplit the supplied material into the real-world SUBJECTS a specialist should advise on. The host has\n12\talready read every supplied document into `documents`; `request`, `sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`,\n13\tand `specialistFacts` are also in scope, and the source text is authoritative over the short summary.\n14\t\n15\t**You do not carry the splitting rules yourself — they live in loadable knowledge, so the right\n16\theuristic for THIS kind of material is always available.** Work in two reads, then resolve:\n17\t\n18\t1. **See the menu + the default axis.** `await loadKnowledge('organizing', 'split')` returns the index:\n19\t   the universal rule (a specialist is a subject the user would ASK for advice on; a category of their\n20\t   own records — costs, dates, payments, photos, contacts, a list/tracker/dashboard/overview — is app\n21\t   DATA, a table, never a specialist) and the list of available domain guides.\n22\t2. **Load the guide(s) for this material.** From what `documents` actually contain and what `request`\n23\t   asks, decide which listed domain(s) the material spans, and load each:\n24\t   `await loadKnowledge('organizing', 'split', '<domain>')` (a mixed pile loads several; use `'default'`\n25\t   when none of the listed domains fit). Read that guidance — it tells you the axis this domain splits\n26\t   on and which of its parts are subjects vs. mere records.\n27\t\n28\tThen split accordingly and emit exactly ONE `currentTask.resolve({ scopes: [...] })`. For each scope\n29\temit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object with `topic`,\n30\t`executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and empty `sources` (supplied material is not web\n31\tresearch). Ground every finding only in the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`. Combine parts\n32\tthat serve one continuous purpose; do not split a subject merely because it carries several kinds of\n33\trecords; each supplied fact belongs to one scope only."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_xceELgSEMbLiZDXxIvlOMHdS","session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"1a195439-48a9-44ae-9329-c7884041e7b7","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:25:07.978Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder structural failure"}
