{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_RH94WIpauZRKJ0UPeHbqCaJZ","type":"tool_result","content":"120\t/** Lightweight metadata for listSessions() — never exposes the Session object. */\n121\texport interface SessionMeta {\n122\t  sessionId: string;\n123\t  spaceDir: string;\n124\t  agentSlug: string;\n125\t  lastActivity: number;\n126\t  started: boolean;\n127\t  status: SessionStatus;\n128\t}\n129\t\n130\t/** Parameters for spinning up one session's wiring (mirrors bin.ts web branch). */\n131\texport interface BuildSessionArgs {\n132\t  spaceDir: string;\n133\t  agentSlug: string;\n134\t  /** Project id + absolute project root (`<root>/<projectId>`), set in project mode so the\n135\t   *  session's app globals resolve against the project. */\n136\t  projectId?: string;\n137\t  projectRoot?: string;\n138\t  /** The project's booted app-global impls (db store, …). Injected into the session VM +\n139\t   *  its forks/delegates when the agent holds the matching capability grants. */\n140\t  appGlobals?: AppGlobalImpls;\n141\t  /** Project-generated typed `apiCall` overloads (Phase 4) for the agent's DTS. */\n142\t  appDts?: string;\n143\t  model?: string;\n144\t  budget?: {\n145\t    maxEpisodes?: number;\n146\t    maxToolCalls?: number;\n147\t    maxForkDepth?: number;\n148\t    maxWallClockMs?: number;\n149\t  };\n150\t  renderHost: WebRenderHost;\n151\t  /** Optional NDJSON trace file (headless runs may want a trace on disk). */\n152\t  traceFile?: string;\n153\t  /** Override the always-loaded system space dirs (absolute paths). */\n154\t  systemSpaceDirs?: string[];\n155\t  /** Absolute space dirs pre-loaded into dynamicSpaces at start. */\n156\t  preloadSpaceDirs?: string[];\n157\t  /** Absolute path to the project's spaces/ dir; exposed to VMs as env. */\n158\t  projectSpacesDir?: string;\n159\t  /** The project's `functions/*.ts` (third function scope), loaded from\n160\t   *  `<projectRoot>/functions/` and injected into the project-rooted session +\n161\t   *  its forks. Original TS source + esbuild-bundled ESM (when the project has\n162\t   *  node_modules). Absent for legacy (non-project) sessions. */\n163\t  projectFunctions?: Record<string, string>;\n164\t  projectFunctionsBundled?: Record<string, string>;\n165\t  /** True for INTERACTIVE sessions (create/resume — a client answers asks over\n166\t   *  the WS). Gates the consent prompter (plan S10): headless runs leave this\n167\t   *  unset so consent-marked calls fail closed instead of hanging on an ask\n168\t   *  no client will ever answer. */\n169\t  interactive?: boolean;\n170\t}\n171\t\n172\t/** Encapsulates the bin.ts wiring: construct a Session bound to the chosen\n173\t *  streamFn. The manager owns the entry's hub and subscribes it to the returned\n174\t *  session's tracer, so each session's events stay scoped to its own hub. */\n175\texport type BuildSession = (args: BuildSessionArgs) => Session;\n176\t\n177\texport interface SessionManagerOpts {\n178\t  streamFn: (opts: StreamOpts) => Promise<StreamSession>;\n179\t  defaultSpaceDir?: string;\n180\t  maxSessions?: number;\n181\t  snapshotsDir?: string;\n182\t  idleTtlMs?: number;\n183\t  /** Encapsulates the bin.ts wiring (construct Session bound to a streamFn). The\n184\t   *  manager pairs each session with its OWN WebRenderHost + TraceHub. When\n185\t   *  omitted, a default builder using `streamFn` is used. */\n186\t  buildSession?: BuildSession;\n187\t  /** Absolute path to `<cwd>/.lmthing`. When set, the manager resolves project\n188\t   *  directories from this root and exposes project CRUD methods. */\n189\t  lmthingRoot?: string;\n190\t  /** Resolved default model spec (e.g. \"azure:DeepSeek-V4-Flash\") used when a\n191\t   *  session is created without an explicit model override. Forwarded as\n192\t   *  `modelAlias` so llm_request/llm_response events carry a model field for\n193\t   *  cost tracking. */\n194\t  defaultModelAlias?: string;\n195\t}\n196\t\n197\t\n198\t/** Parse a `space/agent#action` spawn ref → the pieces `runHeadless` wants\n199\t *  (mirrors the hook `parseTrigger`). No `#` ⇒ the whole ref is the space, no action. */\n200\tfunction parseAgentRef(ref: string): { spaceRef: string; agentSlug: string; action: string } {\n201\t  const hash = ref.indexOf('#');\n202\t  const spaceRef = hash >= 0 ? ref.slice(0, hash) : ref;\n203\t  const action = hash >= 0 ? ref.slice(hash + 1) : '';\n204\t  const agentSlug = spaceRef.split('/').pop() ?? spaceRef;\n205\t  return { spaceRef, agentSlug, action };\n206\t}\n207\t\n208\t/** Best-effort JSON for embedding spawn input into the agent's kickoff message. */\n209\tfunction safeStringify(v: unknown): string {\n210\t  try {\n211\t    return JSON.stringify(v);\n212\t  } catch {\n213\t    return String(v);\n214\t  }\n215\t}\n216\t\n217\t/** Run a project api endpoint by name and unwrap it to a value/throw — the\n218\t *  agent-facing `apiCall` contract (mirrors the runtime's internal resolver): a\n219\t *  ≥400 status becomes a thrown Error carrying `.status`, else the body is returned. */\n220\tasync function unwrapApiCall(rt: ApiRuntime, name: string, input?: unknown): Promise<unknown> {\n221\t  const res = await rt.callByName(name, input);\n222\t  if (res.status >= 400) {\n223\t    const body = res.body as { error?: { message?: string } } | undefined;\n224\t    const err = new Error(body?.error?.message ?? `apiCall(\"${name}\") failed`) as Error & { status?: number };"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"0dc5fbb9-4c92-4b8e-b96b-822e57a2af08","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:30:49.297Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/session-manager.ts","content":"/** Lightweight metadata for listSessions() — never exposes the Session object. */\nexport interface SessionMeta {\n  sessionId: string;\n  spaceDir: string;\n  agentSlug: string;\n  lastActivity: number;\n  started: boolean;\n  status: SessionStatus;\n}\n\n/** Parameters for spinning up one session's wiring (mirrors bin.ts web branch). */\nexport interface BuildSessionArgs {\n  spaceDir: string;\n  agentSlug: string;\n  /** Project id + absolute project root (`<root>/<projectId>`), set in project mode so the\n   *  session's app globals resolve against the project. */\n  projectId?: string;\n  projectRoot?: string;\n  /** The project's booted app-global impls (db store, …). Injected into the session VM +\n   *  its forks/delegates when the agent holds the matching capability grants. */\n  appGlobals?: AppGlobalImpls;\n  /** Project-generated typed `apiCall` overloads (Phase 4) for the agent's DTS. */\n  appDts?: string;\n  model?: string;\n  budget?: {\n    maxEpisodes?: number;\n    maxToolCalls?: number;\n    maxForkDepth?: number;\n    maxWallClockMs?: number;\n  };\n  renderHost: WebRenderHost;\n  /** Optional NDJSON trace file (headless runs may want a trace on disk). */\n  traceFile?: string;\n  /** Override the always-loaded system space dirs (absolute paths). */\n  systemSpaceDirs?: string[];\n  /** Absolute space dirs pre-loaded into dynamicSpaces at start. */\n  preloadSpaceDirs?: string[];\n  /** Absolute path to the project's spaces/ dir; exposed to VMs as env. */\n  projectSpacesDir?: string;\n  /** The project's `functions/*.ts` (third function scope), loaded from\n   *  `<projectRoot>/functions/` and injected into the project-rooted session +\n   *  its forks. Original TS source + esbuild-bundled ESM (when the project has\n   *  node_modules). Absent for legacy (non-project) sessions. */\n  projectFunctions?: Record<string, string>;\n  projectFunctionsBundled?: Record<string, string>;\n  /** True for INTERACTIVE sessions (create/resume — a client answers asks over\n   *  the WS). Gates the consent prompter (plan S10): headless runs leave this\n   *  unset so consent-marked calls fail closed instead of hanging on an ask\n   *  no client will ever answer. */\n  interactive?: boolean;\n}\n\n/** Encapsulates the bin.ts wiring: construct a Session bound to the chosen\n *  streamFn. The manager owns the entry's hub and subscribes it to the returned\n *  session's tracer, so each session's events stay scoped to its own hub. */\nexport type BuildSession = (args: BuildSessionArgs) => Session;\n\nexport interface SessionManagerOpts {\n  streamFn: (opts: StreamOpts) => Promise<StreamSession>;\n  defaultSpaceDir?: string;\n  maxSessions?: number;\n  snapshotsDir?: string;\n  idleTtlMs?: number;\n  /** Encapsulates the bin.ts wiring (construct Session bound to a streamFn). The\n   *  manager pairs each session with its OWN WebRenderHost + TraceHub. When\n   *  omitted, a default builder using `streamFn` is used. */\n  buildSession?: BuildSession;\n  /** Absolute path to `<cwd>/.lmthing`. When set, the manager resolves project\n   *  directories from this root and exposes project CRUD methods. */\n  lmthingRoot?: string;\n  /** Resolved default model spec (e.g. \"azure:DeepSeek-V4-Flash\") used when a\n   *  session is created without an explicit model override. Forwarded as\n   *  `modelAlias` so llm_request/llm_response events carry a model field for\n   *  cost tracking. */\n  defaultModelAlias?: string;\n}\n\n\n/** Parse a `space/agent#action` spawn ref → the pieces `runHeadless` wants\n *  (mirrors the hook `parseTrigger`). No `#` ⇒ the whole ref is the space, no action. */\nfunction parseAgentRef(ref: string): { spaceRef: string; agentSlug: string; action: string } {\n  const hash = ref.indexOf('#');\n  const spaceRef = hash >= 0 ? ref.slice(0, hash) : ref;\n  const action = hash >= 0 ? ref.slice(hash + 1) : '';\n  const agentSlug = spaceRef.split('/').pop() ?? spaceRef;\n  return { spaceRef, agentSlug, action };\n}\n\n/** Best-effort JSON for embedding spawn input into the agent's kickoff message. */\nfunction safeStringify(v: unknown): string {\n  try {\n    return JSON.stringify(v);\n  } catch {\n    return String(v);\n  }\n}\n\n/** Run a project api endpoint by name and unwrap it to a value/throw — the\n *  agent-facing `apiCall` contract (mirrors the runtime's internal resolver): a\n *  ≥400 status becomes a thrown Error carrying `.status`, else the body is returned. */\nasync function unwrapApiCall(rt: ApiRuntime, name: string, input?: unknown): Promise<unknown> {\n  const res = await rt.callByName(name, input);\n  if (res.status >= 400) {\n    const body = res.body as { error?: { message?: string } } | undefined;\n    const err = new Error(body?.error?.message ?? `apiCall(\"${name}\") failed`) as Error & { status?: number };","numLines":105,"startLine":120,"totalLines":2479}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_045500d6-9aa4-4118-8380-9ad02f87837b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_WGIp7ZPm0mREtL0C6Qgjssl9","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/10-implement_pages.md","old_string":"---\nid: implement_pages\noutput:\n  route: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [plan_pages, plan_endpoints, plan_components, implement_components]\nforEach: plan_pages.pages\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nWrite ONE React page into the LIVE project's `pages/`. Your page is in `item` =\n{ route, purpose, endpoints, components } (`index` is the home; `items/[id]` is a dynamic route).\n`plan_endpoints.endpoints` and `plan_components.components` are in scope. Write the FULL `.tsx` source\ninline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern (real line breaks).\n\nWiring rules — the app fails to compile if you break them:\n- Import data hooks ONLY from `@app/runtime` (`useApi`/`useApiMutation`/`apiCall`/`Link`/`useParams`) —\n  never `fetch` a raw URL, and NEVER import `react-router`, `@radix-ui/*`, `@agent-chat/react`, or a\n  relative `use-api`; none exist in a generated project.\n- Read data by passing an endpoint `name` to `useApi` — the exact stable id the endpoint exported. Use\n  ONLY names listed for this page in `item.endpoints` (each is a real `plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`);\n  never invent or transform a name. Every read endpoint returns `{ items: [...] }`, so read `data.items`.\n- IMPORT the reusable components you planned, by relative path from `pages/` to `components/`: a\n  top-level page uses `../components/<Name>`, a page one directory deep uses `../../components/<Name>`.\n- STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`,\n  `border-border`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color.\n\n`writeProjectPage` validate