{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_YCy5g3GmJEoolufpjVkJwNCT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/**\n2\t * App-capability parsing for agent `instruct.md` frontmatter (`capabilities:`).\n3\t *\n4\t * A `capabilities:` value is a YAML list whose entries are either a **bare\n5\t * capability id** (full scope) or a **single-key map** carrying that\n6\t * capability's config (narrowed scope):\n7\t *\n8\t * ```yaml\n9\t * capabilities:\n10\t *   - db:read: { tables: [sources, raw_items] }   # narrowed to named tables\n11\t *   - db:write: { tables: [raw_items] }           # per-VERB scope\n12\t *   - api:call: { allow: [webSearch, markRead] }  # allowlist IS the config (required)\n13\t *   - connections:use: { providers: [google, slack] } # provider allowlist (required)\n14\t *   - pages:write                                 # bare = full scope, no config\n15\t * ```\n16\t *\n17\t * Validation is **fail-loud** (mirrors `validateKnowledgeOptionFrontmatter` in\n18\t * `load.ts`: a module-level allow-list `Set` + an unknown-key throw): an unknown\n19\t * capability id, an unknown config key, a `db:*` `tables` naming a table absent\n20\t * from the project's `database/` (only when `knownTables` is supplied), a bare\n21\t * `api:call` (its `allow` is required — there is no \"call anything\"), or a\n22\t * config given to a bare-only cap all throw.\n23\t */\n24\t\n25\texport type CapabilityId =\n26\t  | 'db:read'\n27\t  | 'db:write'\n28\t  | 'db:schema'\n29\t  | 'pages:write'\n30\t  | 'api:write'\n31\t  | 'hooks:write'\n32\t  | 'api:call'\n33\t  | 'connections:use'\n34\t  | 'knowledge:write'\n35\t  | 'project:manage'\n36\t  | 'store:read'\n37\t  | 'store:install'\n38\t  | 'events:emit'\n39\t  | 'fs:scratch';\n40\t\n41\t/** Every recognized capability id. Unknown ids fail the space load. */\n42\texport const CAPABILITY_IDS: ReadonlySet<CapabilityId> = new Set<CapabilityId>([\n43\t  'db:read',\n44\t  'db:write',\n45\t  'db:schema',\n46\t  'pages:write',\n47\t  'api:write',\n48\t  'hooks:write',\n49\t  'api:call',\n50\t  'connections:use',\n51\t  'knowledge:write',\n52\t  'project:manage',\n53\t  'store:read',\n54\t  'store:install',\n55\t  'events:emit',\n56\t  'fs:scratch',\n57\t]);\n58\t\n59\t/** The three db verbs whose (optional) config narrows scope to `{ tables: [...] }`. */\n60\texport const DB_CAPABILITY_IDS: ReadonlySet<CapabilityId> = new Set<CapabilityId>([\n61\t  'db:read',\n62\t  'db:write',\n63\t  'db:schema',\n64\t]);\n65\t\n66\t/**\n67\t * Knowledge-write scope. A present `knowledge:write` cap lets an agent author knowledge\n68\t * option files (`writeKnowledge`) into its OWN space by default; `spaces` is a future\n69\t * allow-list of ADDITIONAL space keys it may write into. Only own-space is enforced today\n70\t * — the runtime binds the write path to the running agent's space dir (see\n71\t * `createWriteKnowledgeGlobal`); the `spaces` list is parsed and reserved for when\n72\t * cross-space writes ship.\n73\t */\n74\tfunction parseKnowledgeWriteConfig(config: unknown, ctx: ParseCapabilitiesCtx): { spaces?: string[] } {\n75\t  if (!isRecord(config)) {\n76\t    throw new Error(\n77\t      `Agent \"${ctx.agentId}\" capability \"knowledge:write\" has an invalid config: expected a map like { spaces: [...] }`,\n78\t    );\n79\t  }\n80\t  const unknownKeys = Object.keys(config).filter((k) => k !== 'spaces');\n81\t  if (unknownKeys.length > 0) {\n82\t    throw new Error(\n83\t      `Agent \"${ctx.agentId}\" capability \"knowledge:write\" has disallowed config key(s): ${unknownKeys.join(', ')}. Allowed key: spaces`,\n84\t    );\n85\t  }\n86\t  if (!('spaces' in config)) return {};\n87\t  const rawSpaces = config['spaces'];\n88\t  if (!Array.isArray(rawSpaces) || rawSpaces.some((s) => typeof s !== 'string')) {\n89\t    throw new Error(\n90\t      `Agent \"${ctx.agentId}\" capability \"knowledge:write\" config \"spaces\" must be a list of space keys`,\n91\t    );\n92\t  }\n93\t  return { spaces: rawSpaces as string[] };\n94\t}\n95\t\n96\t/** Authoring/store/event caps that are **bare-only** — a config payload is an error. */\n97\tconst BARE_ONLY_CAPABILITY_IDS: ReadonlySet<CapabilityId> = new Set<CapabilityId>([\n98\t  'pages:write',\n99\t  'api:write',\n100\t  'hooks:write',\n101\t  'project:manage',\n102\t  'store:read',\n103\t  'store:install',\n104\t  'events:emit',\n105\t  'fs:scratch',\n106\t]);\n107\t\n108\t/**\n109\t * The parsed capability model attached to a loaded agent. A present key means\n110\t * the cap is GRANTED; its value carries the (optional) scope narrowing:\n111\t *   - `db:*`         → `{ tables?: string[] }` (omitted `tables` = all tables)\n112\t *   - `api:call`     → `{ allow: string[] }` (always present — required)\n113\t *   - `connections:use` → `{ providers: string[] }` (always present — required)\n114\t *   - `knowledge:write` → `{ spaces?: string[] }` (omitted = own space only; the\n115\t *                      `spaces` allow-list is reserved for cross-space writes — not\n116\t *                      yet enforced, own-space is bound host-side)\n117\t *   - authoring      → `true` (bare, no config)\n118\t *   - project:manage → `true` (bare; grants createProject/selectProject — the\n119\t *                      appbuilder's authority to scaffold/select a catalog app)\n120\t *   - store:read     → `true` (bare; grants storeSearch/storeInspect — catalog discovery)\n121\t *   - store:install  → `true` (bare; grants the consent-marked installSpace)\n122\t *   - events:emit    → `true` (bare; grants emitEvent — publish the OWN scope's\n123\t *                      declared events into the hook pipeline)\n124\t *   - fs:scratch     → `true` (bare; grants createScratch + a sandboxed generic\n125\t *                      fs/shell surface rooted at a throwaway .lmthing/scratch dir —\n126\t *                      the engineer's code sandbox. The ONLY grant that earns any\n127\t *                      generic filesystem access; every other agent persists via the\n128\t *                      typed writeProject* / architect builder functions.)\n129\t */\n130\texport interface AppCapabilities {\n131\t  'db:read'?: { tables?: string[] };\n132\t  'db:write'?: { tables?: string[] };\n133\t  'db:schema'?: { tables?: string[] };\n134\t  'pages:write'?: true;\n135\t  'api:write'?: true;\n136\t  'hooks:write'?: true;\n137\t  'api:call'?: { allow: string[] };\n138\t  'connections:use'?: { providers: string[] };\n139\t  'knowledge:write'?: { spaces?: string[] };\n140\t  'project:manage'?: true;\n141\t  'store:read'?: true;\n142\t  'store:install'?: true;\n143\t  'events:emit'?: true;\n144\t  'fs:scratch'?: true;\n145\t}\n146\t\n147\texport interface ParseCapabilitiesCtx {\n148\t  /** Agent slug, for actionable error messages. */\n149\t  agentId: string;\n150\t  /**"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ab428b-0827-4b0f-9cdb-3f06c26238c4","uuid":"b3b5d777-d28c-4201-b800-46be10c7748d","timestamp":"2026-07-16T19:37:31.650Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/spaces/capabilities.ts","content":"/**\n * App-capability parsing for agent `instruct.md` frontmatter (`capabilities:`).\n *\n * A `capabilities:` value is a YAML list whose entries are either a **bare\n * capability id** (full scope) or a **single-key map** carrying that\n * capability's config (narrowed scope):\n *\n * ```yaml\n * capabilities:\n *   - db:read: { tables: [sources, raw_items] }   # narrowed to named tables\n *   - db:write: { tables: [raw_items] }           # per-VERB scope\n *   - api:call: { allow: [webSearch, markRead] }  # allowlist IS the config (required)\n *   - connections:use: { providers: [google, slack] } # provider allowlist (required)\n *   - pages:write                                 # bare = full scope, no config\n * ```\n *\n * Validation is **fail-loud** (mirrors `validateKnowledgeOptionFrontmatter` in\n * `load.ts`: a module-level allow-list `Set` + an unknown-key throw): an unknown\n * capability id, an unknown config key, a `db:*` `tables` naming a table absent\n * from the project's `database/` (only when `knownTables` is supplied), a bare\n * `api:call` (its `allow` is required — there is no \"call anything\"), or a\n * config given to a bare-only cap all throw.\n */\n\nexport type CapabilityId =\n  | 'db:read'\n  | 'db:write'\n  | 'db:schema'\n  | 'pages:write'\n  | 'api:write'\n  | 'hooks:write'\n  | 'api:call'\n  | 'connections:use'\n  | 'knowledge:write'\n  | 'project:manage'\n  | 'store:read'\n  | 'store:install'\n  | 'events:emit'\n  | 'fs:scratch';\n\n/** Every recognized capability id. Unknown ids fail the space load. */\nexport const CAPABILITY_IDS: ReadonlySet<CapabilityId> = new Set<CapabilityId>([\n  'db:read',\n  'db:write',\n  'db:schema',\n  'pages:write',\n  'api:write',\n  'hooks:write',\n  'api:call',\n  'connections:use',\n  'knowledge:write',\n  'project:manage',\n  'store:read',\n  'store:install',\n  'events:emit',\n  'fs:scratch',\n]);\n\n/** The three db verbs whose (optional) config narrows scope to `{ tables: [...] }`. */\nexport const DB_CAPABILITY_IDS: ReadonlySet<CapabilityId> = new Set<CapabilityId>([\n  'db:read',\n  'db:write',\n  'db:schema',\n]);\n\n/**\n * Knowledge-write scope. A present `knowledge:write` cap lets an agent author knowledge\n * option files (`writeKnowledge`) into its OWN space by default; `spaces` is a future\n * allow-list of ADDITIONAL space keys it may write into. Only own-space is enforced today\n * — the runtime binds the write path to the running agent's space dir (see\n * `createWriteKnowledgeGlobal`); the `spaces` list is parsed and reserved for when\n * cross-space writes ship.\n */\nfunction parseKnowledgeWriteConfig(config: unknown, ctx: ParseCapabilitiesCtx): { spaces?: string[] } {\n  if (!isRecord(config)) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Agent \"${ctx.agentId}\" capability \"knowledge:write\" has an invalid config: expected a map like { spaces: [...] }`,\n    );\n  }\n  const unknownKeys = Object.keys(config).filter((k) => k !== 'spaces');\n  if (unknownKeys.length > 0) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Agent \"${ctx.agentId}\" capability \"knowledge:write\" has disallowed config key(s): ${unknownKeys.join(', ')}. Allowed key: spaces`,\n    );\n  }\n  if (!('spaces' in config)) return {};\n  const rawSpaces = config['spaces'];\n  if (!Array.isArray(rawSpaces) || rawSpaces.some((s) => typeof s !== 'string')) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Agent \"${ctx.agentId}\" capability \"knowledge:write\" config \"spaces\" must be a list of space keys`,\n    );\n  }\n  return { spaces: rawSpaces as string[] };\n}\n\n/** Authoring/store/event caps that are **bare-only** — a config payload is an error. */\nconst BARE_ONLY_CAPABILITY_IDS: ReadonlySet<CapabilityId> = new Set<CapabilityId>([\n  'pages:write',\n  'api:write',\n  'hooks:write',\n  'project:manage',\n  'store:read',\n  'store:install',\n  'events:emit',\n  'fs:scratch',\n]);\n\n/**\n * The parsed capability model attached to a loaded agent. A present key means\n * the cap is GRANTED; its value carries the (optional) scope narrowing:\n *   - `db:*`         → `{ tables?: string[] }` (omitted `tables` = all tables)\n *   - `api:call`     → `{ allow: string[] }` (always present — required)\n *   - `connections:use` → `{ providers: string[] }` (always present — required)\n *   - `knowledge:write` → `{ spaces?: string[] }` (omitted = own space only; the\n *                      `spaces` allow-list is reserved for cross-space writes — not\n *                      yet enforced, own-space is bound host-side)\n *   - authoring      → `true` (bare, no config)\n *   - project:manage → `true` (bare; grants createProject/selectProject — the\n *                      appbuilder's authority to scaffold/select a catalog app)\n *   - store:read     → `true` (bare; grants storeSearch/storeInspect — catalog discovery)\n *   - store:install  → `true` (bare; grants the consent-marked installSpace)\n *   - events:emit    → `true` (bare; grants emitEvent — publish the OWN scope's\n *                      declared events into the hook pipeline)\n *   - fs:scratch     → `true` (bare; grants createScratch + a sandboxed generic\n *                      fs/shell surface rooted at a throwaway .lmthing/scratch dir —\n *                      the engineer's code sandbox. The ONLY grant that earns any\n *                      generic filesystem access; every other agent persists via the\n *                      typed writeProject* / architect builder functions.)\n */\nexport interface AppCapabilities {\n  'db:read'?: { tables?: string[] };\n  'db:write'?: { tables?: string[] };\n  'db:schema'?: { tables?: string[] };\n  'pages:write'?: true;\n  'api:write'?: true;\n  'hooks:write'?: true;\n  'api:call'?: { allow: string[] };\n  'connections:use'?: { providers: string[] };\n  'knowledge:write'?: { spaces?: string[] };\n  'project:manage'?: true;\n  'store:read'?: true;\n  'store:install'?: true;\n  'events:emit'?: true;\n  'fs:scratch'?: true;\n}\n\nexport interface ParseCapabilitiesCtx {\n  /** Agent slug, for actionable error messages. */\n  agentId: string;\n  /**","numLines":150,"startLine":1,"totalLines":347}}}
